## âœ… Definitions

- [x] **Cloud model** â€“ The deployment type of cloud resources (how and where they are delivered).
- [x] **Private cloud** â€“ Cloud services used by a **single organization**. Greater control, higher cost. Hosted on-site or in a dedicated off-site facility.
- [x] **Public cloud** â€“ Services offered by **third-party providers** over the internet, available to anyone. Most scalable and cost-effective.
- [x] **Hybrid cloud** â€“ Combines **private and public** cloud environments. Useful for burst traffic, security flexibility, and app placement decisions.
- [x] **Multi-cloud** â€“ Usage of **multiple public cloud providers** (e.g., Azure + AWS). Can be strategic or transitional.
- [x] **Azure Arc** â€“ Azureâ€™s management solution for hybrid and multi-cloud environments. Helps manage servers, Kubernetes clusters, and apps across environments.
- [x] **Azure VMware Solution** â€“ Allows you to run VMware workloads on Azure without refactoring.

